    "body": "### Problem\n\nEntering the float before getting back to the window may have an added effect\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean \n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(0, false, { relative = \"editor\", height = 50, width = 50, col = 50, row = 20 })\n\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n-- lua\n\n-- lua\n```\n\n\nthe --lua lines are just added to have enough lines for scrolling. \n\nluafile% to open the window \nCtrl-w w \nCtrl-w w\n\nScroll to observe the effect on the cursor\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe cursor should behave as it usually does when no float is open\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1092+g0da4d89558\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nfedora 40\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
